exploits.secure_fix:
Use Anchor's `Program<'info, T>` type which auto-validates the program ID:
```rust
pub token_messenger_minter_program_data: Program<'info, Token>,
```
For custom programs, define the CPI interface:
```rust
#[derive(Clone)]
pub struct MyProgram;
impl anchor_lang::Id for MyProgram {
fn id() -> Pubkey { my_program::ID }
}
pub token_messenger_minter_program_data: Program<'info, MyProgram>,
```

exploits.ai_explanation:
Anchor security analyzer identified Missing CPI Guard violation. Cross-Program Invocations on Solana execute arbitrary programs. The runtime does not validate that the target program is the one the developer intended. If the CPI target is an unvalidated AccountInfo, an attacker deploys a malicious program that implements the same instruction interface and passes it as the program field. The Crema Finance exploit ($8.8M, July 2022) used exactly this technique.. Recommended fix: Use Anchor's `Program<'info, T>` type which auto-validates the program ID:
```rust
pub token_messenger_minter_program_data: Program<'info, Token>,
```
For custom programs, define the CPI interface:
```rust
#[derive(Clone)]
pub struct MyProgram;
impl anchor_lang::Id for MyProgram {
fn id() -> Pubkey { my_program::ID }
}
pub token_messenger_minter_program_data: Program<'info, MyProgram>,
```

